SIMPLE: metamorphic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metamorphic
<hw>Met`a*mor"phic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Metamorphosis</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Subject to change;
changeable; variable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Causing a change of structure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, produced by, or
exhibiting, certain changes which minerals or rocks may have undergone
since their original deposition; -- especially applied to the
recrystallization which sedimentary rocks have undergone through the
influence of heat and pressure, after which they are called
<xex>metamorphic</xex> rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metamorphism</ent>⟦br⟧
